1255â†’// ApplyConfig applies a new config to the DB.
1256â†’// Behaviour of 'OutOfOrderTimeWindow' is as follows:
1257â†’// OOO enabled = oooTimeWindow > 0. OOO disabled = oooTimeWindow is 0.
1258â†’// 1) Before: OOO disabled, Now: OOO enabled =>
1259â†’//   - A new WBL is created for the head block.
1260â†’//   - OOO compaction is enabled.
1261â†’//   - Overlapping queries are enabled.
1262â†’//
1263â†’// 2) Before: OOO enabled, Now: OOO enabled =>
1264â†’//   - Only the time window is updated.
1265â†’//
1266â†’// 3) Before: OOO enabled, Now: OOO disabled =>
1267â†’//   - Time Window set to 0. So no new OOO samples will be allowed.
1268â†’//   - OOO WBL will stay and will be eventually cleaned up.
1269â†’//   - OOO Compaction and overlapping queries will remain enabled until a restart or until all OOO samples are compacted.
1270â†’//
1271â†’// 4) Before: OOO disabled, Now: OOO disabled => no-op.
